# =============================================================================
# AOS v3 — local env (copy to agents_os_v3/.env). Gitignored. TikTrack-isolated.
# =============================================================================
#
# Cursor / agents: do NOT paste secrets into chat. Put the URL only in this file.
# The repo .cursorignore excludes agents_os_v3/.env from AI file context; agents
# can still run shell on YOUR machine, e.g.:
#   bash -c 'set -a && source agents_os_v3/.env && set +a && python3 agents_os_v3/seed.py'
#
# zsh / terminal: after "cp .env.example .env", open .env in an editor and fill
# AOS_V3_DATABASE_URL. Do NOT paste Hebrew/English comment lines into the shell
# as commands. Optional Docker vars go in this file only — never type "AOS_V3_DOCKER_*"
# at the prompt (zsh treats * as a glob and errors with "no matches found").
#
# =============================================================================

# Required — set this line to your AOS-only Postgres (must not be the TikTrack app database):
# Example (edit values): postgresql://myuser:mypass@127.0.0.1:5432/aos_v3
AOS_V3_DATABASE_URL=

# Pipeline domain slug "tiktrack" in definition.yaml / seed is a registry row only, not this URL.

# Optional: Python venv for init script (else agents_os_v3/.venv, else python3 on PATH)
# AOS_V3_VENV=/absolute/path/to/venv

# Optional: CREATE DATABASE via docker exec — uncomment and set real names (in THIS file only)
# AOS_V3_DB_NAME=aos_v3
# AOS_V3_DOCKER_PG_CONTAINER=my_postgres_container
# AOS_V3_DOCKER_PSQL_USER=postgres
# AOS_V3_DOCKER_PSQL_ADMIN_DB=postgres

# Optional API CORS
# ALLOWED_ORIGINS=http://localhost:8090,http://127.0.0.1:8090

# After AOS_V3_DATABASE_URL is set (and TikTrack api/.env exists):
#   python3 scripts/verify_dual_domain_database_connectivity.py
